1. Information We Collect
We do not collect or store Personally Identifiable Information (PII). However, we may collect the following types of non-identifiable data:
Usage Data:
Information about how you interact with our Apps, such as features accessed, session durations, and error reports.
Device Information:
Information about the device used to access our Apps, such as operating system, device type, and app version.
2. How We Use Collected Information
The information we collect is used to:
Enhance Analytics:
Understand app performance and usage trends.
Improve Product Performance:
Diagnose issues, identify improvements, and optimize functionality.
Personalize Experiences:
Tailor the app experience to suit user preferences and behaviors.
Support Marketing:
Provide insights for promoting our Apps and services effectively.
3. Sharing of Information
We may share certain information with third-party partners for the following purposes:
OpenAI Services:
Some usage data may be shared with OpenAI to provide AI-driven functionalities within our Apps. OpenAI retains such data for 30 days for processing and quality assurance before deletion.
Analytics and Ads:
We may share usage data with third parties to facilitate analytics, marketing tracking, and advertising services.
We do not sell or disclose your information to other third parties unless required by law.
4. Data Retention
OpenAI Data:
Retained for 30 days by OpenAI and then deleted.
Other Usage Data:
Retained by us for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this policy.
5. Security Measures
We take reasonable administrative, technical, and physical safeguards to protect your data from unauthorized access, loss, misuse, or alteration. While we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your information, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure.
6. Your Choices
You can limit data collection by:
Adjusting app permissions on your device.
Disabling certain features within the app.
Uninstalling the app if you no longer wish to use our services.
7. Updates to this Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The updated policy will be posted on our website with a new effective date. Please review this policy periodically for changes.
8. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, you can contact us at:
Email:
support@mindblownapp.com